      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 209: The scoped services `clearSwarmBodyOverwriteConversation` and `bodyOverwriteLoadedConversation` do not authorize that the calling plugin is enabled for the supplied account/conversation. Any plugin that can call these services can clear or trigger body-overwrite processing for arbitrary conversations, unlike the global variants above that use `getEnabledConversationsForPlugin(plugin)`. Pass the `plugin` argument through and reject unauthorized pairs before touching the conversation.\n\n```suggestion\nauto clearSwarmBodyOverwriteConversation \u003d [this](const DLPlugin* plugin, void* data) {\n    auto* p \u003d static_cast\u003cstd::pair\u003cstd::string, std::string\u003e*\u003e(data);\n    if (!p)\n        return -1;\n    if (!getEnabledConversationsForPlugin(plugin).count(*p)) {\n        JAMI_WARNING(\"clearSwarmBodyOverwriteConversation: plugin not enabled for {}/{}, rejecting\", p-\u003efirst, p-\u003esecond);\n        return -1;\n    }\n    ...\n};\n```",
