      "message": "[Critical] Line 407: `getEnabledConversationsForPlugin()` associates handlers with a plugin using substring matching: `handler-\u003eid().find(rootPath) !\u003d std::string::npos`. This can match unrelated paths such as `/plugins/foo` and `/plugins/foobar`, giving the wrong plugin authorization over conversations. Compare normalized parent paths for equality instead.\n\n```suggestion\nconst auto handlerRoot \u003d handler-\u003eid().substr(0, handler-\u003eid().find_last_of(DIR_SEPARATOR_CH));\nif (handlerRoot \u003d\u003d rootPath) {\n    handlerPtrs.insert(reinterpret_cast\u003cuintptr_t\u003e(handler.get()));\n    handlerNames.insert(handler-\u003egetChatHandlerDetails().at(\"name\"));\n}\n```",
